  abstract={The prevalence of suicide ideation presents a critical societal concern, demanding innovative approaches for intervention and prevention. In response, I propose a developed deep learning model tailored for identifying depression level of an individual and predict the suicidal tendency. Traditional approaches often overlook the multimodal emotional data from social media and the impact of fluctuating emotions in temporal relationships which is a major factor contributing to suicidal thoughts, AFTM aims to integrate multivariate data from Instagram of a specific individual, encompassing emotional and temporal feature to capture the complexity inherent in this phenomenon.},
