  booktitle={2023 International Workshop on Artificial Intelligence and Image Processing (IWAIIP)}, 
  title={Recognition of Facial Expressions and Emotions on the Face using the YOLOv5 Algorithm}, 
  year={2023},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={337-341},
  abstract={This study examines the significant influence of emotional states on individuals, recognizing that people are often confronted with numerous challenges and problems in their lives. Such challenges can give rise to feelings of despair and tension, especially in those who struggle to manage them effectively. Depression, which is not just limited to adults, can also have a significant impact on children who may not fully grasp their socio-economic conditions. One of the serious consequences of unresolved emotional distress, particularly depression, is an elevated risk of suicide. Within this framework, facial recognition technology presents itself as a powerful instrument for identifying human emotions. The purpose of this study is to assess the efficacy of facial recognition systems in detecting indicators of depression. Using the YOLOv5 algorithm and comparing it with its precursors, YOLOv4 and YOLOv7, the research conducts a simulation experiment to examine the ability of the system to precisely interpret a range of emotional states, including happiness, sadness, and anger. The research findings suggest that the YOLO algorithm, particularly in its most recent versions, displays exceptional precision in identifying and classifying intricate facial expressions, thus showcasing its potential as a beneficial device in mental health evaluations.},
